President Obama has proclaimed September 15th to October 15th as National Hispanic Heritage Month. He highlights the contributions of the Hispanic community to the United States, including their service in the military and government, their participation in the economy, and their pursuit of education and higher aspirations. The President also emphasizes his commitment to providing opportunities for Hispanics to achieve the American dream, such as supporting Hispanic-owned small businesses, investing in education, and expanding access to healthcare. He mentions his efforts to fix the broken immigration system and calls on Congress to pass comprehensive immigration reform. The proclamation concludes by encouraging public officials, educators, and all Americans to observe the month with appropriate ceremonies and activities.